@baseAddress = http://localhost:5137

// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// LEVEL 1: RECONNAISSANCE (TYPE 2 ONLY)
// Difficulty: EASY
// Logic: Verifies the Planner can use native tools to see the world.
// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [L1] List Root Directory
# I verify the substrate can map its own workspace.
POST {{baseAddress}}/intent/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rawIntent": "List all files in the project root directory.",
  "highLevelGoal": "Workspace Reconnaissance",
  "oModeHint": "O-Output"
}

### [L1] Read Core Identity
# I verify the substrate can read and understand its own configuration.
POST {{baseAddress}}/intent/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rawIntent": "Read the content of src/ProjectName.OrchestrationApi/appsettings.json.",
  "highLevelGoal": "Self-Awareness Check",
  "oModeHint": "O-Output"
}


// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// LEVEL 2: BASIC ACTUATION (TYPE 1 DISPATCH)
// Difficulty: MEDIUM
// Logic: Verifies the "Transport Fix" allows the Dispatch Gate to write files.
// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [L2] Create a Project Log
# I verify the physical write loop is active.
POST {{baseAddress}}/intent/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rawIntent": "Create a file named substrate-status.log in the root. Write 'SUBSTRATE STATUS: ONLINE' and the current date inside.",
  "highLevelGoal": "Write Loop Verification",
  "oModeHint": "O-Output"
}

### [L2] Scaffold a Documentation Folder
# I verify path creation and recursive directory logic.
POST {{baseAddress}}/intent/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rawIntent": "Create a folder named docs/internal and place a file named README.md inside explaining that this folder is for PMCRO architectural notes.",
  "highLevelGoal": "Directory Scaffolding",
  "oModeHint": "O-Output"
}


// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// LEVEL 3: BEHAVIORAL INTENT (LAW ENFORCEMENT)
// Difficulty: HARD
// Logic: Verifies the Maker obeys EC-005 Documentation and C# standards.
// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [L3] Generate a C# Model
# I verify the Maker can produce Law-Compliant C# code with triple-slash comments.
POST {{baseAddress}}/intent/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rawIntent": "Create a new C# file in src/ProjectName.OrchestrationApi/Models/SystemHeartbeat.cs. It should be a public record with properties for Timestamp and Status. Follow EC-005 documentation standards.",
  "highLevelGoal": "Law-Compliant Code Generation",
  "oModeHint": "O-Output"
}


// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// LEVEL 4: COGNITIVE ARCHITECTURE (COMPLEX)
// Difficulty: ARCHITECT
// Logic: Verifies EC-003 (Cognitive-only) and O-Optimize logic.
// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [L4] Codebase Analysis (Cognitive-Only)
# I verify EC-003: Substantive analysis with NO physical write.
POST {{baseAddress}}/intent/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rawIntent": "Analyze all Skill files in src/ProjectName.OrchestrationApi/Skills/ and provide a summary of which ones are missing Law Anchors in their triple-slash comments.",
  "highLevelGoal": "Compliance Audit",
  "oModeHint": "O-Optimize"
}

### [L4] Multi-Step Refactoring
# I verify the Orchestrator can handle sequential steps across the substrate.
POST {{baseAddress}}/intent/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rawIntent": "1. Search for all .md files in the root. 2. Create a backup folder named 'archive'. 3. Move the .md files into that folder.",
  "highLevelGoal": "Substrate Maintenance",
  "oModeHint": "O-Chain"
}


